<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Hello one and all,
<br />
       I recently bit the bullet and instead of joining the WoW bandwagon of players to leave Everquest, I decided to go ahead and renew my account. With that said, i'm finding it EXTREMELY hard nowadays to get threw the 50s. I used to play my enchanter on the side alittle, and was able to get him all the way to 55 pretty quickly. However, since my return to the game, its been nearly impossible to find groups! People playing in their 50s / lower 60s tend to xp in random locations, and there is no real place you can go to just look for an xp group. The planes have all but completely emptied, and what groups I do get are in the Plane of Valor which it is impossible for me to mez in at my current level, which pretty much renders me useless except as a buff bot.
<br />

<br />
        I was just hoping you guys might be able to shed some incite on my situation, and maybe give me some tips to get me over the hump known as 60. I've read threw the boards now several times, but most posts relating to the subject are all pre-WoW / EQ2 when players were more abundant.
<br />

<br />
       Another thing that I wanted to ask was how much you guys think a charisma upgrade will help my charming routine. My charisma now is currently around 220, but I still haven't geared my Enchanter for the long haul yet. How much would the upgrade from 220 to 255 help with the extension of charms?
<br />

<br />
        Thanks for any help in advance, and good luck to all!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
